beer.beer_name: Rare Breed: Rye Fighter Double IPA
beer.beer_description:
This brew is dedicated to Ryu, hero of Street Fighter.
Ryu means ‘plentiful and abundant’, which coincidentally, is also how we would
describe the hop levels in this beer.
Hadouken charges of energy from Cryo-hops make for Shoryuken levels of hop
intensity, tempered by gentle spicy notes from the malted rye.

APPEAR ANCE:
Golden with slight haze.
AROMA:
Hop driven with pine, tropical fruit and
stone fruit aromas from the neutral yeast
strain.
FL AVOUR:
Medium bodied with spicy notes and
coating mouthfeel from rye malt. Strong
bitterness with a dry finish.

items.badge_description: Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 70 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 15!

Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 70 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 15!
Do you come from the land down under, where beer does flow, and men chunder? That's at least 100 different beers from Australia. Try 5 more for Level 21.
